WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.635
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.670 --> 00:05.037
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.072 --> 00:06.571
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.606 --> 00:09.241
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.276 --> 00:11.476
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.511 --> 00:13.545
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.580 --> 00:15.881
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:15.916 --> 00:17.215
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.250 --> 00:18.917
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:18.952 --> 00:20.386
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:26.259 --> 00:28.293
[ Calliope music plays ]

00:29.062 --> 00:31.530
Step right up, folks!
Step right up!

00:31.565 --> 00:33.899
Come see the adorable bears
for sale!

00:33.934 --> 00:35.367
Just 25 cents!

00:35.402 --> 00:36.535
For free, even!

00:36.570 --> 00:38.370
Whatever fits
into your budget.

00:38.405 --> 00:40.572
All right, bros,
- time to step up our game.

00:40.607 --> 00:42.240
Do a cute pose,
Pan Pan.

00:42.275 --> 00:45.043
[ Drum roll ]

00:45.078 --> 00:46.445
Adorable!

00:46.480 --> 00:47.846
Now you, little bro!

00:47.881 --> 00:50.182
[ Drum roll ]

00:50.217 --> 00:52.751
Oh! So adorable!

00:52.786 --> 00:55.420
Hey, mister, want to buy
three adorable bears

00:55.455 --> 00:56.955
for 25 cents?

00:56.990 --> 00:58.757
Huh? Oh, uh...

00:58.792 --> 01:00.025
All:
Yeah! Yeah! Do it! Do it!

01:00.060 --> 01:01.560
-Come on! Come on!
-Please! Please!

01:01.595 --> 01:03.528
-Wait! No, no, no!
-Over here! Over here!

01:03.563 --> 01:04.863
-Over here!
-Yeah! Us!

01:04.898 --> 01:06.865
-Pick us!
-Wait, wait! No, no, no!

01:06.900 --> 01:09.134
-Yeah, us, us!
-Over here! Over here!

01:09.169 --> 01:10.368
-Come on, pick us!

01:10.403 --> 01:12.270
[ Coin clanks, whirring ]

01:12.305 --> 01:15.574
<i>You are making great</i>
<i>financial decisions today.</i>

01:15.609 --> 01:17.076
Oh, sweet!

01:18.078 --> 01:19.044
Gah!

01:19.079 --> 01:20.879
Every single time!

01:20.914 --> 01:22.814
Curse you,
psychic machine!

01:22.849 --> 01:24.549
Oaaah! Aaaah!

01:24.584 --> 01:26.384
Dang, Grizz,
you're strong!

01:26.419 --> 01:27.953
Have you been
working out?

01:27.988 --> 01:29.321
Oh, uh, yeah, man.

01:29.356 --> 01:30.489
Feel my 'ceps.

01:30.524 --> 01:31.823
Whoa!

01:31.858 --> 01:33.391
Toned.

01:33.426 --> 01:35.293
Hey, mister,
want to feel my muscles?

01:35.328 --> 01:36.728
Man: No.

01:36.763 --> 01:39.631
[ Sighs ] Not even my muscles
can get us adopted.

01:39.666 --> 01:41.399
[ Sighs ]
[ Sighs ]

01:41.434 --> 01:43.235
[ Girl giggling ]

01:43.270 --> 01:44.236
Huh?     Huh?

01:44.271 --> 01:45.237
What is it, bro?

01:45.272 --> 01:47.172
[ Giggling ]

01:47.207 --> 01:49.608
I love him!
Thank you!

01:49.643 --> 01:51.944
I'm gonna name him Vavi!

01:53.613 --> 01:54.679
That's it, guys!

01:54.714 --> 01:56.248
We just got to become
game prizes,

01:56.283 --> 01:58.950
and somebody is bound to want us
and take us home.

01:58.985 --> 02:00.519
I'm so smart!

02:00.554 --> 02:02.187
Let's roll.

02:02.222 --> 02:03.421
Stupid psychic machine.

02:03.456 --> 02:04.589
[ Grunts ]

02:04.624 --> 02:06.491
Why do people
even like you?

02:06.526 --> 02:07.592
So dumb.

02:07.627 --> 02:08.627
[ Whirring ]

02:08.662 --> 02:10.696
<i>You will never be adopted.</i>

02:11.898 --> 02:14.099
All right, let's see
what we have here.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.267
[ Balloon pops ]

02:15.302 --> 02:16.935
What about that one?

02:16.970 --> 02:18.470
Panda:
Looks too hard.

02:18.505 --> 02:19.671
Maybe that one?

02:19.706 --> 02:20.872
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

02:20.907 --> 02:22.607
That one's scary.
You're right.

02:22.642 --> 02:25.110
Hmm. Okay, let's see.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.845
What's the easiest game?

02:26.880 --> 02:29.481
This is the easiest game!

02:29.516 --> 02:31.383
Um, ball toss!

02:31.418 --> 02:32.784
Test your skills.

02:32.819 --> 02:35.887
Uh, ball toss --
y-you take the ball a-and toss.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.123
Even a pet fish
could do it!

02:38.158 --> 02:39.357
[ Crying ]

02:39.392 --> 02:41.626
Oh, my gosh. D-Did something
happen to your fish?

02:41.661 --> 02:43.495
I'm so sorry.

02:43.530 --> 02:44.629
[ Groans ]

02:44.664 --> 02:46.198
Wow.
What a loser.

02:46.233 --> 02:47.499
He's perfect!

02:47.534 --> 02:49.534
All right, bros,
stay professional.

02:49.569 --> 02:51.670
[ Bones crack ]

02:53.840 --> 02:55.407
[ Whimpering ] Ball toss.

02:55.442 --> 02:57.876
Toss a ball. Please?

02:57.911 --> 03:00.512
Oh, man. You really got to
work on your sales pitch.

03:00.547 --> 03:01.980
Aah! What the --

03:02.015 --> 03:03.515
Oh, man,
don't do that.

03:03.550 --> 03:04.749
What do you guys want?

03:04.784 --> 03:09.187
We can help you, you know,
uh...Louise?

03:09.222 --> 03:10.822
It's, uh, "Lewis."

03:10.857 --> 03:12.224
It says it right here.

03:12.259 --> 03:13.825
Hey!
We can read!

03:13.860 --> 03:16.761
Um, okay, look, you guys
really can't stand there.

03:16.796 --> 03:19.064
My dear Lewis, what Pan Pan
is trying to say

03:19.099 --> 03:20.865
is that we can help
bring in customers.

03:20.900 --> 03:22.834
What?!
[ Laughs ]

03:22.869 --> 03:24.035
How are you gonna --

03:24.070 --> 03:26.037
[ Inhales deeply ]
No, no, no, no.

03:26.072 --> 03:29.007
I am not gonna listen to some baby bears.
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:29.042 --> 03:30.742
Oh, wow!
Are those the prizes?

03:30.777 --> 03:32.510
Aww,
they're so cute!

03:32.545 --> 03:33.845
I-I-I'm sorry?

03:33.880 --> 03:36.114
Yes, those bears --
are they the prizes?

03:36.149 --> 03:37.182
Um...no.

03:37.217 --> 03:38.250
We can be the prizes.

03:38.285 --> 03:39.351
Try to win us.

03:39.386 --> 03:40.752
Only $2
to play the game.

03:40.787 --> 03:43.922
Wow! Only $2?
- That's such a great deal.

03:43.957 --> 03:46.458
Yeah, we'd totally play
for those bears.

03:46.493 --> 03:47.459
For sure.

03:47.494 --> 03:49.361
Uh, r-r-really?

03:49.396 --> 03:52.597
Um, could you excuse us
for a moment?

03:52.632 --> 03:55.033
All right, bears,
I'll make you a deal --

03:55.068 --> 03:57.969
you can stay if you help
bring in customers.

03:58.004 --> 04:00.038
Well, just until
someone wins us, right?

04:00.073 --> 04:01.373
We're trying
to get adopted.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.874
Huh? Adopted?

04:02.909 --> 04:04.542
Oh, yeah. Sure. Right.

04:04.577 --> 04:06.211
Okay, Lewis,
you got a mic?

04:06.246 --> 04:07.646
And some fresh beats?

04:07.681 --> 04:09.381
Uh, yeah,
I think so.

04:09.416 --> 04:12.217
All right, you got yourself
a deal, Lewis.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.385
Deal.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.254
Hmm. Strong grip.

04:16.523 --> 04:18.757
[ Click, hop-hop music plays ]

04:22.262 --> 04:23.895
Aww, yeah!

04:23.930 --> 04:25.964
Coming
straight from the fair.

04:25.999 --> 04:28.066
Playing games
and taking names.

04:28.101 --> 04:30.001
You want to be next?
Tell 'em, Pan!

04:30.036 --> 04:33.905
Both:
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

04:33.940 --> 04:35.573
[ Rapping ]
♪ It's Pan Pan coming up first ♪

04:35.608 --> 04:38.576
♪ You should win the game
by the end of this verse ♪

04:38.611 --> 04:41.446
♪ Kickin' mad rhymes,
never, ever rehearsed ♪

04:41.481 --> 04:42.914
♪ It's time to get to work ♪

04:42.949 --> 04:45.250
♪ Take your best shot,
try hard ♪

04:45.285 --> 04:47.252
♪ Win the prize,
take us home to your backyard ♪

04:47.287 --> 04:49.187
♪ You like bears?
Everybody does ♪

04:49.222 --> 04:51.856
♪ Take a look at my little bro,
covered in fuzz ♪

04:51.891 --> 04:53.491
♪ Three bears
barely breaking a sweat ♪

04:53.526 --> 04:55.927
♪ Everybody's jockin' us
'cause we're the best ♪

04:55.962 --> 04:57.796
♪ But I'm already
talkin' too much ♪

04:57.831 --> 04:59.431
♪ Let me let my bro
get some of this flava ♪

04:59.466 --> 05:01.599
Yeah, boyyyy!

05:01.634 --> 05:04.202
Okay, okay,
nobody's won yet,

05:04.237 --> 05:06.204
but you're looking
super-lucky today.

05:06.239 --> 05:08.440
Let's see if you can
give it a try.

05:08.475 --> 05:09.541
♪ Play the game ♪

05:09.576 --> 05:11.443
♪ Three balls, three tries ♪

05:11.478 --> 05:13.178
♪ Three bears, your prize ♪

05:13.213 --> 05:14.979
♪ You could take us home
right now ♪

05:15.014 --> 05:17.515
♪ Come on, Grizz, get on the mic
and tell 'em how ♪

05:17.550 --> 05:20.118
♪ Anyone can play this game,
just watch, now ♪

05:20.153 --> 05:22.320
♪ Take a throw,
and the balls get knocked down ♪

05:22.355 --> 05:23.822
♪ It's easy as 1, 2, 3 ♪

05:23.857 --> 05:26.291
♪ Step 3 being taking bears
home, you see ♪ Come on!

05:26.326 --> 05:28.460
♪ Step right up,
just take a chance ♪

05:28.495 --> 05:30.962
♪ You could win big-time,
cancel all plans ♪

05:30.997 --> 05:32.630
♪ There's nothing more important
you gotta do ♪

05:32.665 --> 05:35.133
♪ than pay the man,
throw the ball, and win, too ♪

05:35.168 --> 05:37.535
♪ When it comes to prizes,
bears are the best ones ♪

05:37.570 --> 05:39.804
♪ Not stuffed, but the kind
that can have fun ♪

05:39.839 --> 05:41.473
You know,
let's show these nice people

05:41.508 --> 05:43.208
what real fun looks like!

05:43.243 --> 05:46.077
♪ Play the game ♪ Bust it, Grizz!
Bust it, Grizz! Bust it!

05:46.112 --> 05:48.179
Kick it, Pan! Kick it, Pan!
Kick it!

05:48.214 --> 05:50.315
Go, little bro!
Go, little bro! Go!

05:50.350 --> 05:52.650
Go, little bro!
Go, little bro! Go!

05:52.685 --> 05:54.819
Bust it, Grizz! Bust it, Grizz!
Bust it!

05:54.854 --> 05:56.921
Kick it, Pan! Kick it, Pan!
Kick it!

05:56.956 --> 05:59.023
Go, little bro!
Go, little bro! Go!

05:59.058 --> 06:01.893
Go, little bro!
Go, little bro! Go!

06:03.530 --> 06:04.729
Waaaaaugh!

06:04.764 --> 06:06.364
Please, people!
It ain't that hard!

06:06.399 --> 06:08.266
Is our dancing
not inspiring enough?

06:08.301 --> 06:10.235
Okay, you actually have
muscles.

06:10.270 --> 06:12.437
Come on!
Win it -- for us!

06:12.472 --> 06:13.772
[ Grunts ]

06:13.807 --> 06:15.107
[ Clank ]

06:17.877 --> 06:19.511
How could this be?!

06:19.546 --> 06:20.912
Augggggh!

06:20.947 --> 06:23.014
Wow, kid, you're strong.
You bench?

06:23.049 --> 06:24.716
I not bench.
I bear.

06:24.751 --> 06:26.184
Now begone with you!

06:26.219 --> 06:28.019
[ Sighs ]
Dang it, Pan Pan.

06:28.054 --> 06:30.054
I just want to be won
so bad.

06:30.089 --> 06:32.791
I know. We just got to be
patient, I guess.

06:32.826 --> 06:35.360
So, should we dance again
or something?

06:35.395 --> 06:36.828
Both: Huh?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.133
[ All grunting ]

06:42.168 --> 06:43.201
Hmm.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.702
[ Grunts ]

06:44.737 --> 06:47.372
Ow!
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

06:47.407 --> 06:49.207
What the heck?

06:49.242 --> 06:50.208
[ Gasps ]

06:50.243 --> 06:51.943
Lewis,
what is this baloney?

06:51.978 --> 06:53.378
This is rigged!

06:53.413 --> 06:56.581
Hey, hey, hey!
Um, pipe down, you pipsqueaks.

06:56.616 --> 06:58.049
Yeah, the game is rigged,

06:58.084 --> 07:00.919
but we can't have people
just go and win everything.

07:00.954 --> 07:02.887
T-That's just bad business.

07:02.922 --> 07:04.489
W-What?!
You cheater!

07:04.524 --> 07:05.723
You -- You sneak!

07:05.758 --> 07:06.958
You -- You...

07:06.993 --> 07:08.460
[ Bell dinging ]

07:08.495 --> 07:09.961
...dingle!

07:09.996 --> 07:13.064
Hey, man, this is a
family-friendly establishment.

07:13.099 --> 07:14.799
But if no one ever wins,

07:14.834 --> 07:16.734
that means
we'll never be adopted.

07:16.769 --> 07:18.403
Yeah, well, too bad.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.473
You're bringing in the moolah,
so you're staying here!

07:21.508 --> 07:23.141
No! We don't have to
listen to you!

07:23.176 --> 07:25.777
You're not our dad!
Nobody is!

07:25.812 --> 07:27.612
Come on, bros.
Let's go elsewhere.

07:28.615 --> 07:30.915
[ Up-tempo music plays,
girls laughing ]

07:30.950 --> 07:32.284
<i>Oh, Lewis.</i>

07:33.620 --> 07:35.587
I-I-I can't allow that!

07:35.622 --> 07:38.656
You're staying,
whether you like it or not!

07:38.691 --> 07:40.925
Wha-- No!
Let us down!

07:40.960 --> 07:41.993
Help! Grizz!

07:42.028 --> 07:43.261
[ Laughs evilly ]

07:43.296 --> 07:45.096
Grizzly:
You can't do this, you cretin!

07:45.131 --> 07:46.998
I-I won't stand for it!

07:47.800 --> 07:48.766
Aw, beans.

07:48.801 --> 07:50.368
[ Grunts ]

07:50.403 --> 07:51.836
-Hey, come on, you little rascal!
-Get away from me!

07:51.871 --> 07:53.605
Uh, Grizz, watch out!
Go left! Go left!

07:53.640 --> 07:56.140
Oh, no, no, no,<i> my</i> left!
Ha! Gotcha!

07:56.175 --> 07:58.276
What's happening? What is
that man doing with that child?

07:58.311 --> 07:59.611
Oh, man,
I wish I could take

07:59.646 --> 08:01.212
a picture with my phone
or something.

08:01.247 --> 08:02.614
Young woman:
- Should we call the police?

08:02.649 --> 08:04.282
Is this stranger danger?
Hush!

08:04.317 --> 08:07.685
Hey, now, no need for that.
Everything's good.

08:07.720 --> 08:09.053
We're just playing.

08:09.088 --> 08:10.622
[ Laughs nervously ]

08:10.657 --> 08:12.023
Hey, kid, hush your face,

08:12.058 --> 08:15.026
or it'll be, uh, curtains
for your brothers.

08:15.061 --> 08:16.995
N-No! No curtains!

08:18.364 --> 08:19.464
Oh, how distasteful!

08:19.499 --> 08:21.733
If only I could
win them back myself!

08:21.768 --> 08:22.901
Psh! What?!

08:22.936 --> 08:25.136
[ Laughs ]
"Win them back." No way!

08:25.171 --> 08:26.905
You'd have to be
the strongest person ever

08:26.940 --> 08:28.640
to knock them down,
and you're, like, a kid.

08:28.675 --> 08:30.875
Kids aren't usually that strong,
you know, so...

08:30.910 --> 08:33.244
Strong, eh? Hmm.

08:33.279 --> 08:37.382
All right, Lewis, I'll try,
and if I win, I get my bros.

08:37.417 --> 08:38.583
No backsies!

08:38.618 --> 08:40.351
Well...okay.

08:40.386 --> 08:43.855
And if you lose,
you stay with me<i> forever!</i>

08:43.890 --> 08:46.925
Or at least till the summer job
is over, so, like, two months.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.327
Do we have a deal?

08:49.362 --> 08:50.662
[ Sighs ]

08:50.697 --> 08:52.430
Psych! [ Laughs ]

08:52.465 --> 08:54.999
I've never been able
to do that before.

08:55.034 --> 08:57.369
♪♪

09:02.542 --> 09:04.342
[ Laughs evilly ]

09:04.377 --> 09:06.177
[ Whimpers ]

09:06.212 --> 09:08.280
[ Sighs ]
You can do this, Grizz.

09:09.882 --> 09:11.449
Come on,
you little bench boy.

09:11.484 --> 09:12.450
[ Grunting ]

09:12.485 --> 09:13.785
Panda:
We believe in you, Grizz!

09:13.820 --> 09:15.186
Remember your workouts

09:15.221 --> 09:17.922
and your so very,
very toned muscles!

09:17.957 --> 09:18.890
Right!

09:18.925 --> 09:20.792
Tone. Muscles. Strength.

09:20.827 --> 09:23.194
Power. Weight. Protein.

09:23.229 --> 09:24.195
Uh, abs.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.297
Get on with it,
already!

09:26.332 --> 09:28.333
♪♪

09:32.572 --> 09:34.239
[ Laughs evilly ]

09:35.441 --> 09:36.808
Rrrrr...

09:36.843 --> 09:38.243
Raaaah!

09:40.647 --> 09:42.714
[ Slo-mo ] Whoa!

09:42.749 --> 09:44.449
All: [ Slo-mo ] Wow.

09:47.854 --> 09:49.120
[ Clank ]
Whoa!

09:49.155 --> 09:50.722
[ Squeals ]

09:50.757 --> 09:51.723
All: Ooh!

09:51.758 --> 09:53.959
[ Squealing continues ]

09:57.263 --> 10:00.264
Dang! Nice shot, Grizz!
That was smart.

10:00.299 --> 10:02.400
You know, I was actually aiming
for the bottles.

10:02.435 --> 10:03.901
Oh, wait!
What am I saying?!

10:03.936 --> 10:05.403
I got you, bros!

10:05.438 --> 10:07.438
[ Grunts ]

10:07.473 --> 10:08.506
There you go.

10:08.541 --> 10:10.241
Now, let's blow
this Popsicle stand.

10:10.276 --> 10:12.577
Goodbye, Lewis,
you fraud!

10:12.612 --> 10:14.078
To freedom!

10:14.113 --> 10:16.080
No more of your rigged,
cheating ways!

10:16.115 --> 10:17.815
Whoo-hoo!
Tell them, Pan!

10:17.850 --> 10:19.017
Cheater!

10:19.052 --> 10:20.251
Gosh, they're cute.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.186
Hang on.
Did he say "rigged"?

10:22.221 --> 10:23.755
[ Squealing, groaning ]

10:23.790 --> 10:25.757
-I think he totally rigged it!
-Aw, man, this thing is rigged?

10:25.792 --> 10:27.925
Um...no refunds?

10:27.960 --> 10:29.628
Hey, get that guy!

10:30.797 --> 10:32.263
♪♪

10:32.298 --> 10:33.264
[ Panda sighs ]

10:33.299 --> 10:34.599
Grizz, is it our future

10:34.634 --> 10:37.268
to be taken advantage of
at every turn?

10:37.303 --> 10:40.938
I don't know, Pan,
- but I have a way of finding out.

10:40.973 --> 10:43.141
Listen, sorry about earlier,
my dude.

10:43.176 --> 10:45.176
Please --
tell us something good.

10:45.211 --> 10:46.544
[ Whirring ]

10:46.579 --> 10:48.680
<i>The road ahead will be tough.</i>

10:48.715 --> 10:51.015
<i>But as long</i>
<i>as you stick together,</i>

10:51.050 --> 10:54.486
<i>your future will be</i>
<i>happy and good.</i>

10:59.892 --> 11:02.394
<i>Also, you will live in a cave!</i>

11:04.197 --> 11:06.164
♪♪
